comment.text: Omg amazing food and amazing vibes!! Totally recommend! Their espresso frozen martini was bomb! Me and my friend came here late at night and they stop seating at 10:15, and we prolly got there at 10:12 but the bartender GAREN was ahmazing. He recommended the lobster the crab and a side of risotto and he hit the nail on the head. It was to die for! Highly recommend.  We would come back JUST for Garen. He hooked us up and gave us the best service!

Let me start off by saying I love love love the decor and the vibe here. Gave very Tulum in Atlanta . It's a dark restaurant that is very strict against flash photography & the waitresses will not hesitate in telling you. This is where they lost me because the waitress explained it as an African fusion place that has seasonal menus. Didn't really get African food from menu items (ex sushi& other Asian dishes) the drinks were great and the shrimp tempura rolls I got were very satisfying. I also got the dessert at fruit in a chocolate cup which was super good but the chocolate was so bitter it wasn't enjoyable. Overall would suggest going for the experience but not something I see myself going back to just to go

Yebo's updated location is larger and even trendier than its prior one. Their outdoor area is particularly charming, replete with heat lamps and see-and-be-seen guests who are happen to be frequenting the space on any given night. We, however, dined indoors.

Lots of interesting options on the menu. We had the wild mushroom soup, which was unique in and of itself given the foamy element incorporated into the texture. Truffle oil + shiitake mushroom gave it a daring flair. The ostrich sliders are understandably in the appetizer section, though they are perhaps more filling than they look. The classic Caesar salad and harvest salad provided for a healthy option, and if you'd prefer to be healthy, I'd certainly recommend it, though I've had tastier salads. The halibut tasted fantastic, as did the curried cauliflower. Regarding desserts, to be honest, I was slightly underwhelmed with the pumpkin cheesecake and milk chocolate hazelnut selections...they weren't bad...just not as delectable as I might have anticipated.

Service was great, though our water was left unfilled for quite some time. Other than that, they were friendly and helpful.

Great patio! Love the ambiance and the service was great.
The food very tasty.
The mushroom bursts were really really good as well as the wild mushroom ravioli ( I love mushroom!)
The sea bass was another dish that my husband ordered and he liked it!

1st time trying South African food. Great atmosphere, excellent and flavorful with incredible service. Try the Halibut in curry sauce. I have never had a more flavorful Hummus appetizer. Don't know what they do but the popcorn is great here. Must be the butter.

I joined some family and friends here recently and everyone enjoyed themselves. The new location is beautiful and has a nice courtyard. For starters, we ordered the crab dip, shrimp tempura roll and the bobotie crepes. All of the appetizers were delicious , but the bobotie crepes stood out because it isn't something I'd typically order, but they were really good. The crepes are filled with curry ground beef, raisins, apples and hollandaise. My cocktail, camps bay was really tasty as well. It contained rum and bourbon. For my entree, I chose the Branzino. It was so fresh and flavorful. We ordered a variety of desserts including the strawberry cheesecake, key lime pie and crème brûlée. They were good, not great. I wish they'd bring back the Amarula cheesecake from their old location. It's one of the best desserts I've ever had. 

Everyone enjoyed their food and the service was excellent. Looking forward to returning.

photos.caption: Strawberry cheesecake, creme brûlée and key lime pie
Camps Bay: bourbon, rum, ginger, allspice, apricot and lime

comment.text: This place is very nice.  It should be overlooking the ocean...  the service was very attentive which I can appreciate in these post covid times.   The food was very good , a lot better than I expected .  My only gripe is the food didn't really give me a South African vibe, the menu didn't remind me of South Africa at all.  But with that said the food was definitely good and I would go back .  We had the duck and the lobster.  This place is a bit pricy but worth it.  I loved the location when it was czar bar and cellar 52.  But this place is just as good as those.   There is free valet parking .. just gets better and better lol.

Food was delicious! I had the blackened halibut. The frozen espresso martini was also amazing. The price of the cocktails was a little high but they were strong & tasted really good. Our waitress was really attentive. The vibe and atmosphere are nice! Great for pictures.

Just a wonderful experience at Yebo 

The portions are rather small so if you are hungry order an appetizer if not just the entree will be done 

My party thoroughly enjoyed their drinks also, i had a shirley temple with black cherries DELISH, if you haven't been it's worth your time

Came here for dinner and we sat in the outdoor seating area. I noticed the inside had a very cozy and intimate vibe, dimly lit, as I scoped the scene as we waited to be walked to our table outdoors. Perfect for a date night. The outdoor seating area made me feel like I was on vacation with the trees and tents, like a beach vacation dinner. To start I ordered the tuna roll. For my entree, I ordered the lamb chops they weren't bad once I reheated them at home aka cooked them more, I've definitely had better. My friend ordered the pasta and she said it was very bland which is why she kept drenching it in cheese, she gave it a 6/10. My friend enjoyed her salad + salmon. My other friend ordered the mussels and she seemed to enjoy them as well. We ordered the tiramisu and the cheesecake. I'm not a huge sweets person, but I do love a good cheesecake, this one was pretty good. I didn't taste the tiramisu but they demolished it so I guess it was good. The service was okay, server was pretty forgetful but very sweet.

I would absolutely 100% come back here again! The decor and ambiance is beautiful, the wait staff is attentive, and the food was perfectly prepared.

We went as a party of 6, two adults with four little people in tow. To be clear: this is not a restaurant that gives you the sense it's child-friendly. We went midday on Saturday so the restaurant wasn't packed and we didn't have to feel like we were spoiling every other adult's fun by having the children there.

Almost immediately, the 10 and 12 year old both decided they would prefer fast food after we left. Spoiler alert: all children happily ate off the appetizers and our plates.

Here's what we had:
*Branzino - it was cooked well but not seasoned. Our favorite branzino experiences are places that marinate it; it comes out very flavorful that way. This one was served with a cilantro jalapeño sauce that was absolutely necessary to have it taste anything other than plain and bland.

*Chef's special that had Cornish hen, rice pilaf, and broccolini. It was supposed to come with peri peri sauce but i asked for that on the side to control for spice level. It came with both that and the natural au jus from the "chicken" on the side. The au jus was actually very spicy even though the chicken wasn't. Everything on the plate was cooked well, but the broccolini was really just the tops of the broccolini and there were only 3 pieces on the plate.. Both the 1yo and 3yo ate the chicken and rice with no complaints. 

*Crispy brussel sprouts served with aioli. If you like brussel sprouts (and i do!) there's nothing to complain about here. They were definitely fried crispy and they were a salted well.

 *Fries cooked and seasoned to absolute perfection, served with ketchup and aioli. This was the favorite dish of the 1yo, and the older children ate it too.

*Butternut squash soup. It was creamy and delicious and my 3yo ate half of it. 

Because we were out on a family adventure, I didn't try anything from the drink menu. There were a few small groups of ladies out brunching in cute outfits and full faces. I'd definitely come back all dolled up and enjoy some drinks and dinner!

photos.caption: Foreground: Specialty of the day Background: brussel sprouts
Crab dip and fries (with ketchup and aioli)

comment.text: Such a cute spot with beautiful decor. I literally felt like I was at the beach. The staff were very friendly and recommended trying the Bobotie crepe which consisted of curry beef with raisins and apple slices. The flavor palette was sweet and savory. I also tried the Brussel sprouts and the portion was big enough to share. I really enjoyed my quick drop in and order dinner to go. This restaurant gives you all the feels and is very IG worthy. I'll be back to try a few other dishes soon.

I like everything about this restaurant. The location, the size, the atmosphere, food and the service. It's a smaller place that tend to get loud as more people come in. 
The food was good. I especially enjoyed the Hummus. Wish more Pita came with it.

Came here for a lunch with my girlfriends and was not disappointed. The hostess was a bit nonchalant but other than that had a fantastic time. Our server was very knowledgeable and friendly and made sure we were good and had everything we needed during our entire experience. She made recommendations and really helped us make good decisions on the dishes we chose. I had the salmon and it was delicious. I love olives and capers so this was right up my alley. If you don't they do provide you with the option to remove them or have the sauce on the side. One friend order the lamb chops and I tried a piece of it. It was very tender and seasoned well. I didn't get to try to swordfish it my friend really enjoyed it. We had zero left overs from this meal lol. 

Also, there is free parking and the venue is nice and reminds you of being in a garden outside with the fountain. Great for photos if your into that. We dined outside because the weather was nice but they also offer indoor seating of course. 

Will definitely return to try other dishes.

The best date night experience! Beautiful decor, great drinks and the food is perfect! (Smaller plates but every bite is excellent) 
This could be pricey if you are just going "spur of the moment" .

Took some clients and a colleague for dinner during a recent stay in Atlanta. 

When we arrived the place was very busy and a little loud but the overall atmosphere was very nice. Cleanly decorated and clean over all. We were quickly brought to our table and seated - there were 5 of us.

Our server Camar was very attentive along with the team of others working with him. The menu has something for everyone.

We ordered a few appetizers: mussels, spicy tuna roll, fries, burrata, and ostrich sliders - everything was excellent and the ostrich sliders tasted like beef as our server had advised; a very lean and flavorful beef.

The cocktails and wines that were suggested we also very good :)

I don't remember all the meals but everyone enjoyed them. My only complaint was that my branzino while flavorful had a lot of bones. Based on my question on preparation I expected maybe a few but they did get in the way of me enjoying my meal. I knew this was a risk.

Food was great. We had the crab dip for the appetizer and the filet and the sea bass. Cocktails were great too! The service was subpar for a $$$ restaurant. The wait staff hovered a lot and it was annoying. The music was SO loud I had to scream at the people I was sitting right next to. Felt like I was in a lounge and not a restaurant.

Food was good. The ambience is what I came for. We had calamari, sushi and Mac and
Cheese. Everything was so tasty. It's definitely a rich bitch look with a young adult crowd.
The courtyard was beautiful great for a date and or to take photos. Menu had just enough but not too much to be overwhelming. Our waiter was great I wish I remembered his name.
Reservations were honored. Valet outside in a relatively small shopping center esque place right in buckhead

The food was very mid, the ambiance was nice and fancy, and the service from our server was good. The working manager when we visited however was extremely passive aggressive and dismissed our concerns we had from their undercooked food. For a place that's supposed to be fine dining, everything was literally just "fine"

I have eaten here a few times, unfortunately my last visit was by far the worst. After being seated it took the waitress at least 10 min to come over.We ordered the crab dip for dinner, it came out cold. I ordered the lamb chops for dinner, they were over cooked. I sent them back, the 2nd time still overcooked. The waitress never came back to even check. My spousd ordered the Halibut, it was cold  and lacked the normal flavor it usually has. Given all this going wrong,  no manager ever comes and checks on us. Then to top it off, once she brings the bill she stuff we never even ordered and had an attitude when we showed it to her on the bill. I'm not sure if it was our late time coming or what. But our dinner yesterday, was by far one of my worst dinning experience. I won't be going back
This place is cute, aesthetically pleasing. I didn't care for the food. The menu is limited and the food just wasn't anything special. If anything, the food seemed undercooked.

Loved  my girlfriend and I came for lunch on a random Wednesday. It was a small crowd of gentlemen at the bar. I had a few glasses of white and the Branzino which was amazing but they burned one side of the fish. It was so badly burnt I couldn't eat it. The nerve of the manager to tell me to eat under the skin. Fool! The skin is the best part. They gave me half off my meal. Overall enjoyable, I'll try again.

To sum it up, I left hungry and unsatisfied. 

I had the crab and lobster cake with a Caesar salad (subbed instead of the salad that came with it). This meal was average at best. Nothing stood out for me. The sprite was even watered down. I swapped the Shirley Temple (Sprite + grenadine) for a lemonade which was ok. I did have the vanilla gelato was good though. 

To be fair, my friend loved her oysters and cauliflower. So maybe it was my choice in food. 

The service and atmosphere was great. The server was super friendly and responsive. The atmosphere is cool and laidback. Everything was clean. 

The parking is pretty convenient. Not a ton of parking spaces but enough to find a spot (at least during an early lunch). 

Prices are pretty high for the quality of food I received. I expected the prices but expected the food to be better. 

Overall I think this place is probably good for some, just not for me.

photos.caption: Caesar Salad & Crab and Lobster Cake

comment.text:
Classy dining spot. Contrary to what most people say, I thought it was easy to find. You can opt for valet or self parking around the back. Service was great! We spent a pretty penny but it was worth it. 

Experience: 10/10
Loved the service! Our server, Tiffony was exceptional. The decor is gorgeous. The inside table has pillows which were a nice touch. It was pretty chilly inside especially if you were seated right under a vent but it didn't take too much away from the experience.

Food: 10/10
The food was absolutely amazing. We started with the cheesy crab dip, ostrich sliders, and shrimp tempura. The shrimp tempura was so good that we had to order another. 

It was well worth the price but definitely not an everyday dining spot for us.

I started with espresso martini (nonfrozen). It was on the rather super sweet side and looked like a cappuccino instead of espresso. Very creamy in flavor. 
As my main entree I had the whole Branzino. My server recommended adding the coconut rice as a side to top robe fish with. Branzino was prepared lovely and the coconut rice was a good compliment. 
Dessert...brown butter gelato...make ya wanna slap ya mama!!!! Definitely a must!!! I'm not a fan of sweets but I couldn't put it down. Simply delectable *inserts chefs kiss*
Food was delicious. I had the sea bass and  recommend it. It was crowded but service was fast

What a great place!!  It took awhile for me to come here but will be back!!

Bobotie crepes
Branzino
Halibut

It was all delicious!!!!

Yebo beach Haus was the perfect place to celebrate my sisters birthday. I ordered the Filet Mignon and crab dip and my sister ordered the scallops and they were amazing. I also ordered the frozen expresso martini which was strong but good. The service was also great. Our servers Tiffany and Jonathan were great at giving recommendations and truly catered to our every need. The only thing I would recommend for those going with a big party is to make sure everyone shows up on time or else you will have to wait for your entire group to arrive before being seated. And also get there before 9 pm because they get really packed around that time. The ambiance was great as well. Really cute decor and vibes as well.
Food is consistently delicious and the service is top notch. Although no pictured, we always come back for the bolognese.

photos.caption: Clockwise: Berry Bomb, Keylime Pie, Hazelnut Crunch, Berry Gelato.

comment.text: Came here for a girls dinner night. I was a little disappointed in the food quality for some of the options we chose but the drinks were good & the service was also good. Loved the ambiance as well. The front of the restaurant was deff super cute for photos.

Yebo Beach Haus is located at 56 E Andrews Dr NW in Buckhead. Pull up, valet and walk back thru the inner courtyard to the enjoy drinks and/or a great meal. 

I came here for an afterwork meeting. It was my first time here since they moved to this location down the street and I like the vibe of the place and the neutral styling. 

When you enter thru the doorway, the bar and dining are to your left. Straight ahead you will find the water closet, and just to your right a small waiting area. 

What was ordered:

Appetizers:

Ostrich Sliders*
(Roasted Tomatoes, Arugula, Rosemary Aioli)

Bobotie Crepes
(Sweet & Savory Ground Beef Curry, Apples, Raisins, Hollandaise)

Entrees:

Whole Branzino 
(Grilled Leeks, Grilled Asparagus, Cilantro Jalapeño Sauce)

Halibut
(Red Butter Curry Sauce, Broccolini, Coconut Rice)

Ribeye
(Peri Peri Rub, Roasted Fingerling Potatoes, Caramelized Baby Vegetables, Grilled Corn)

Dessert:
Amarula Cheesecake

Flourless Chocolate Torte

Chocolate Fondue
(Pretzel Bites, Granny Smith Apple, Strawberries)


To Drink:

A bottle of Chocolate Block (Red, South Africa)  
An Old Fashioned (Elijah Craig Bourbon)  


Everything was amazing! 

Especially the Ostrich Sliders! Trust me! Ahh-mazing!

The only thing I wouldn't order again is the Chocolate Fondue. It wasn't bad, it just could be left off the menu. 

Will I be back? Yes, yes, yes, yes, yessssss!

photos.caption: Whole Branzino, Grilled Asparagus, Cilantro Jalapeño Sauce
Halibut, Red Butter Curry Sauce, Broccolini, Coconut Rice

comment.text:
I went here for a bday dinner and was throughly impressed. They have valet parking available. There was also plenty of street parking at the time we went. The ambiance is really nice especially if you sit in the courtyard area.

The service started a little slow but once things started flow we were good. Our waitress was very knowledgeable about the food menu and wine selections. 

I ordered the ribeye and I loved it, although, it was slightly overcooked. 

Overall had a really good experience and would love to go back soon.
Went there for the 1st and the food and ambiance was great. We sat in the bar which is very big with plenty of seats. Definitely be back with friends to try out their other dishes
Went here for my best friends birthday dinner! Ambiance was excellent! Service was excellent! Food was a 10/10 I highly recommend the halibut which is what I had!

Everything about this place is amazing! We actually found it by accident and can truly say that it was the best accident that ever happened. I love a dining experience, and it's definitely held its own!The staff was professional and very accommodating. And I apologize that I don't remember his name, but I waiter who I believed was also a manager was the best. I recommend sitting outside in the square because it is just an escape from reality. In regards to the food- so delicious! I ordered the hummus plate, and my husband ordered the lobster and crab dip. He kept talking about what a wonderful experience. It was there and can't wait to go back. A perfect date night spot!

Came in around 4 on a Saturday and the place was not crowded inside but courtyard seating was full. The decor is such a vibe. I had the frittura mista 4/5 very fresh perfectly fried but didn't taste seasoned. The whole Branzino was highly recommended and I know why! It was perfect. The flavor was out of this world! 5/5 get it! The key lime was mehhh 3/5 the mango was too sweet for me. The service was great. Definitely try this place !

photos.caption: Frittura mista- fried shrimp, halibut, calamari

comment.text: Love this place so much!!! My favorite one is the bobotie crepe! It is so special and I've never had things like that in any other places. The taste of curry goes surprisingly good with the ground beef in it. I'd definitely visit again for this crepe! The whole branzino and the cocktails are also so delicious, but just not as outstanding as the crepe. The only thing I am not very satisfied with was the hummus. It's not even as good as some deli place. But generally this restaurant is really good! And I also love the vibe and decoration. It's definitely a wonderful choice for a decent date night.

photos.caption: bobotie crepes - this plate is curry beef crepe - really really special and delicious!!!!!! Never had this kind of thing before
hummus  - not bad but too ordinary.
Beach haus and frozen espresso martini

comment.text:
I've been wanting to go here for months and oh my god I'm so glad I finally made it in! Yebo is busy, so make sure you get a reservation in. The outside patio is gorgeous with all of the plants around, and the inside varies depending on if it's a summery beach house or a cute Christmas ski lodge. 

For four of us, we started with the shrimp tempera rolls with peri peri sauce. Nothing to rave about, but a good start to the meal.

The stars of the show were the main entrees. I had the special lamb shank and my boyfriend had the bolognese. The lamb was cooked perfectly and it was fall off the bone tender. I tried a bit of the bolognese as well and I loved the homemade sauce and the ostrich ragu.

For dessert, we shared the opera cake with a little bit of raspberry sorbet. The cake was perfect and I loved the little balls of espresso! Overall, Yebo is upscale and we spent over $100 on the meal, but it was totally worth it!

I finally had the opportunity to dine at Yebo Beach Haus and it was absolutely Amazing. The cocktail, appetizer, entree, ambiance and service was excellent; I can't wait to go back and try more items from their menu and experience the transformation that takes place during the winter season.
 
Ambiance - you will feel like you're in a chic beach bungalow, the restaurant and outside courtyard are beautifully decorated.
 
Service - I was immediately greeted by the hostess and received a recommendation to get a drink at the bar while I waited for my party. Our waiter provided five star service, he made recommendations, kept our water glasses filled, and was very thoughtful.
 
Food - the restaurant fuses South African flavors with New American cuisine. I ordered:
Frittura Mista appetizer - $18. Perfectly fried halibut, calamari, prawns served with peri-peri aioli.
Halibut - $32 a nice portion fish in a red butter curry sauce on top of coconut rice with a side of grilled broccolini. I added a little peri-peri sauce to my fish and it was absolutely delicious.
Dessert - I can't recall the name but it was a cheesecake and it was so-so, I would not order it again, not a fan of the texture.
Cocktail - well-made Rosita - $14
I asked for medium and got raw filet mignon. Highly disappointed. The server also never came to check on us so I couldn't send it back. And we waited 45 mins and he finally took our order.

10-10-10 across the freaking board.
Literally not one negative thing I can say about Yebo!
From the decor, drink selection, food and customer service *chefs kiss*
I enjoyed the Chardonnay, coconut rice, grilled branzino. And the mussels TO DIE FOR the sauce was amazing. I could rave about this place all day! If you are on the fence about this place, run don't walk! You won't regret it

Absolutely love my experience here. There is valet at the front but my GPS brought me to the back to a free parking lot. I was attending a private birthday dinner in the back room. It holds About 20-25 people. There was a long table that we sat at. There was a main waiter and he was awesome. I didn't get a chance to ask for anything before he was already bringing it or asking me. He was knowledge about the food and beverage menu which was helpful for my first visit. It's a little loud with the music and chatter but was ok in the private room. In general the restaurant is not big but there's lots of different types of seating from 2 top to small groups and the bar. There is also an outdoor, enclosed area with heat lamps as needed. The birthday dinner was family style so I got to taste alot of the menu. Everything was great. Flavors were right on, not too much, not to little. My fave was the ceasar salad, bootie  crepe, and halibut. The dessert was lacking, kinda just there. My wine that was recommended by the waiter (I don't like dry) was luscious. An aside, the bathrooms are very nice with a "yebo" candle in each which I had to purchae! I recommend everyone coming here. I can't wait to go back and share with friends.

photos.caption: Family style menu that was chosen.
Ceaser salad, takati, mushrooms burratta, bootie crepes

comment.text: Food was flavorful. I especially enjoyed the crab dip and burrata salad. Unfortunately our waiter Jason was very inattentive to our table and chose to spending time with other tables that were noticeably franchised by white patrons. The manager also chose to check on multiple tables franchised by white patrons and ignored us. The discrimination was clear. We will not be returning due to this.

Great tasting food. Strict, "No hat" policy. My wife, after chemo, was told to remove hers because it had a brim like a baseball cap. I was allowed because it was a fedora. Other than that,  a great experience. The food tasted very fresh. Good wine list (Reds). Limited White). 
Our server was great.

photos.caption: Halibut w rice and charred Brussels sprouts.

comment.text: I'm pretty upset at myself for forgetting to take pics of the food (other than the appetizers). YBH is a gem. The decor is stunning and the food is tasty. We tried the sea bass, halibut and the lamb chops.

This is the cutest yet lowkey spot! I was recommended by a friend and I'm so glad I went! There's both indoor and outdoor and the scenery for both is 10/10!

I came with a group of 8 at 4pm, with a reservation. If you're coming as a group, I highly recommend getting one! I believe if you have a group bigger than 9 you may request the private room for events and the likewise.

First, I'd love to give a shout out to our waiter Jamal! It was our first time eating here and he made choosing the right dish so much easier. 10/10 service :)

I ordered the Halibut, but I believe the usual fish they serve with it was unavailable at the time and was replaced with sea bass. Nonetheless, it was great! The curry was seasoned well and went great with the coconut rice and broccolini. Was definitely filling!

Overall, I'd definitely come back here! Great vibes and great food!

My wife and I visited Yebo Beach Haus to celebrate our 3-year anniversary. I've had this restaurant bookmarked for quite some time, so I felt it was the perfect time to make a trip. 

Atmosphere: The atmosphere is AMAZING. I'll be honest, it didn't even feel like we were in Atlanta. It gave very much Miami/LA vibes. We ate outside, which looked even better than the inside. My only issue was my wife and I both got bit by mosquitoes. It would be nice if they have some sort of repellent in the vicinity. Attire is business casual, so don't come inside half stepping on your fashion. This is in Buckhead, so come dressed to impress. 

Parking: Though the website says self-parking and valet, I only noticed valet when we arrived. There's no price for valet, but of course, it is only right to tip.

Service: The service was great! I will say, it seemed to be a delay with our food, but it was pretty busy, so it was fine. The staff's friendliness made up for it. 

Food: For the appetizer, we ordered the FRITTURA MISTA - $16 (lightly breaded halibut / calamari / prawns / peri-peri aioli). SUPER GOOD! Glad our waiter recommended it. For dinner, I ordered the WHOLE BRANZINO - $40 (grilled leeks / grilled asparagus / lemon / cilantro jalapeño sauce). It was so good! The grilled flavor was amazing! This was my first time having fish with the bones & head still attached. It was definitely an experience. I had to take a quick trip to YouTube to see how to successfully de-bone a cooked fish. Lol. The grilled asparagus were good as well. I also ordered the House Cut Fries - $9. So damn delicious! If you like fries, I highly recommend. 

Overall, I loved our dining experience at Yebo Beach Haus.
I sat at the bar and the mussels were amazing.They also have the best espresso martinis in town and they are frozen.Bartenders were very creative.

Celebrated a b'day here about a month ago.  Been coming to Yebo since the restaurant was in Phipps Plaza, then West Paces, and now this new location.  Service a me food spectacular.  The disappointment, a FEE of $40.00 to cut my daughter's cake.  When ask could I cut, the hostess said if brought the cake in it was still $40.00.

The food was average - 4 stars

1 star deducted for tiny mussels. Our waitress mentioned to the manager and he came over to our table and looked at the mussels. I would have thought they would have taken it off of the bill for poor quality. Instead, they just gave some excuse if they don't know what size they get from suppliers. See picture below, literally never seen any mussels so small. I would avoid ordering.
